('chunk_4af7ae96ee39afbc26','file_04bb580a3d99034261','history.md','CROSS-SUBJECT CONNECTIONS','- **Geography (I&S / MYP Geography):** Trade routes, the Silk Route and exploration all depend on **maps, latitude/longitude, coastlines, winds, monsoons and resources**. The geographic factors in empire-building (rivers, defensible borders, ports) connect directly to Geography''s study of location, climate and settlement. The Columbian Exchange links to **biomes, ecosystems and human migration**.
- **Chemistry / Physics (MYP Sciences — for the Scientific Revolution):** Newton''s **laws of motion and gravity** and Galileo''s studies of falling bodies and the **telescope** connect to Physics (forces, motion, optics, astronomy). Renaissance metallurgy, gunpowder and the later development of the scientific method connect to Chemistry and the **experimental method** taught in Sciences. Gupta-era metallurgy (the rust-resistant Iron Pillar) links to Chemistry (corrosion/oxidation).
- **Visual Art (MYP Arts — for the Renaissance):** Renaissance innovations in **linear perspective, proportion, anatomy, chiaroscuro (light and shadow) and realism** are foundational to Visual Art. Studying Leonardo and Michelangelo connects historical context to art techniques, composition and the role of patronage (the Medici) in cultural production.
- **Mathematics:** The Gupta **decimal system and zero**, al-Khwarizmi''s **algebra** in Baghdad, and Renaissance perspective (geometry) all connect History to Mathematics.
- **Language & Literature / Language Acquisition:** OPVL, bias and reliability build critical reading skills; the printing press and the spread of vernacular literature connect to the study of texts and communication.

---
*End of Grade 7 History knowledge base.*','{"cross":1,"subject":1,"connections":1,"geography":3,"myp":3,"trade":1,"routes":1,"the":16,"silk":1,"route":1,"and":18,"exploration":1,"all":2,"depend":1,"maps":1,"latitude":1,"longitude":1,"coastlines":1,"winds":1,"monsoons":1,"resources":1,"geographic":1,"factors":1,"empire":1,"building":1,"rivers":1,"defensible":1,"borders":1,"ports":1,"connect":5,"directly":1,"study":2,"location":1,"climate":1,"settlement":1,"columbian":1,"exchange":1,"links":2,"biomes":1,"ecosystems":1,"human":1,"migration":1,"chemistry":3,"physics":2,"sciences":2,"for":2,"scientific":2,"revolution":1,"newton":1,"laws":1,"motion":2,"gravity":1,"galileo":1,"studies":1,"falling":1,"bodies":1,"telescope":1,"forces":1,"optics":1,"astronomy":1,"renaissance":4,"metallurgy":2,"gunpowder":1,"later":1,"development":1,"method":2,"experimental":1,"taught":1,"gupta":2,"era":1,"rust":1,"resistant":1,"iron":1,"pillar":1,"corrosion":1,"oxidation":1,"visual":2,"art":3,"arts":1,"innovations":1,"linear":1,"perspective":2,"proportion":1,"anatomy":1,"chiaroscuro":1,"light":1,"shadow":1,"realism":1,"are":1,"foundational":1,"studying":1,"leonardo":1,"michelangelo":1,"connects":1,"historical":1,"context":1,"techniques":1,"composition":1,"role":1,"patronage":1,"medici":1,"cultural":1,"production":1,"mathematics":2,"decimal":1,"system":1,"zero":1,"khwarizmi":1,"algebra":1,"baghdad":1,"geometry":1,"history":2,"language":2,"literature":2,"acquisition":1,"opvl":1,"bias":1,"reliability":1,"build":1,"critical":1,"reading":1,"skills":1,"printing":1,"press":1,"spread":1,"vernacular":1,"texts":1,"communication":1,"end":1,"grade":1,"knowledge":1,"base":1}'::jsonb),
